sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Superplasm
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This plasmid was constructed by digesting pLV-TRE-Sox17-Ubc-Bla with SfiI to excise TRE-Sox17, and inserting the PCR SOEd SfiI-Lbx1-T2A-GLRA1-P2A-D5R-SfiI.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This plasmid allows for the simultaneous production of Lbx1 [produces GABAergic neurons], GLRA1 [a glycine receptor], and D5R [a subunit of a particular dopamine receptor]. This makes the neurons able to respond to both a dopamine and a glycine input, and in turn produce a GABA output.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This plasmid was constructed by PCR SOEing.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: iGEM2008 Princeton team

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K076001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Constructed by members of the Weiss Lab.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the backbone plasmid into which SfiI_Ngn1-linker-EYFP-2A-mKate_SfiI was inserted after digestion with SfiI.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The SfiI restriction site must be used in digesting this plasmid. Sox17 must first be removed before this plasmid can effectively serve as a backbone.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Cil Purnick

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K076008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This gene encodes a specific subunit of a dopamine receptor.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Extracted from the source plasmid by PCR.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Available commercially

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K076009
